cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with communication systems and error correction codes.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes the use of machine learning techniques to enhance the E-HARQ feedback scheme.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the feasibility of E-HARQ in different channel conditions and system loads.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes the use of supervised autoencoders for classification.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance of E-HARQ in a system model incorporating scheduling effects.
